div1.p:
IN THE DISTRICT COURT, Of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory, holding Terms at Seattle, for the County of King.
HABEAS CORPUS.
The People of the United States of America, to the Sheriff of King County Greeting: We command you, that you have the body of Jeremiah Mangan by you imprisoned and detained as it is said, together with the time and cause of such imprisonment and detention, by whatsoever name said Jeremiah Mangan shall be called or charged, before the HON. C. H. Hanfrod RICHARD A. JONES Judge of the aforesaid Court at the chambers of the said Judge in the City of Seattle, in said County at the hour of five oclock P.M July 20th 1889 to do and recieve what shall then and there be considered concering him the said Jeremiah Mangan And you have then and there this writ.
Witness the Hon. C. H. Hanford Richard A. Jones Judge of said District Court, and the seal thereof this 19th day of July A. D. 1889. R. M. Hopkins Clerk. By H. T. Harmon Deputy Clerk.

E T No. 6991
In the Distict Court, Third Judicial District, Holding Terms at Seattle, W. T. In the Matter of the Application of Jeremiah Mangan For Writ of Habeas Corpus.
HABEAS CORPUS.
Returned and filed this 20th day of July A. D. 1889 R. M. Hopkins Clerk. By H. T. Harmon Deputy Clerk.
